@startuml C4_Future_Blockchain
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Future Vision - Blockchain for Immutable Audit Trail

Boundary(blockchain, "Blockchain Layer") {
    Component(smart_contract, "SmartContract", "Chain", "Workflow rules")
    Component(audit_chain, "AuditChain", "Ledger", "Immutable log")
    Component(state_channel, "StateChannel", "Off-chain", "Payment efficiency")
}

Boundary(consensus, "Consensus Mechanism") {
    Component(proof_of_stake, "ProofOfStake", "PoS", "Energy efficient")
    Component(byzantine_fault, "ByzantineFaultTolerance", "BFT", "3f+1 nodes")
}

Boundary(privacy, "Privacy & Compliance") {
    Component(zero_knowledge, "ZeroKnowledgeProofs", "Crypto", "Privacy while auditable")
    Component(anonymity, "TransactionAnonymity", "Privacy", "Hide user details")
    Component(gdpr_compliance, "GDPRCompliance", "Erasure", "Right to be forgotten")
}

Boundary(integration, "Integration Points") {
    Component(workflow_events, "WorkflowEvents", "Source", "Task completed")
    Component(chain_writer, "ChainWriter", "Interface", "Write to blockchain")
    Component(chain_reader, "ChainReader", "Interface", "Read from blockchain")
    Component(verification, "Verification", "Audit", "Verify history")
}

Boundary(use_cases, "Use Cases") {
    Component(supply_chain, "SupplyChain", "Traceability", "Product provenance")
    Component(compliance_audit, "ComplianceAudit", "Regulation", "SOX/GDPR proof")
    Component(dispute_resolution, "DisputeResolution", "Legal", "Immutable evidence")
}

smart_contract --> audit_chain: Records to
proof_of_stake --> consensus: Uses
byzantine_fault --> consensus: Alternative
zero_knowledge --> privacy: Provides
workflow_events --> chain_writer: Triggers
chain_writer --> audit_chain: Writes to
audit_chain --> chain_reader: Reads from
chain_reader --> verification: Enables
verification --> compliance_audit: Powers

Note as N1
Blockchain Vision (2027+):

Immutable Audit Trail:
- Every workflow event recorded on blockchain
- Cryptographic proof of sequence
- Cannot be modified retroactively
- Non-repudiation (author accountability)

Smart Contracts:
- Workflow rules embedded in smart contract
- Autonomous execution
- Trust in code, not intermediaries
- Transparent governance

Privacy Considerations:
- Zero-knowledge proofs: Prove without revealing
- Transaction anonymity: Hide user identity
- GDPR compliance: Right to be forgotten
- Privacy-preserving audit trail

Consensus Mechanisms:
- Proof of Stake (PoS): Energy efficient
- Byzantine Fault Tolerance (BFT): Resilient to failures
- Practical Byzantine Fault Tolerance (PBFT): 3f+1 nodes

Use Cases:

Supply Chain Traceability:
- Every shipment step recorded
- Immutable product provenance
- Consumer verification
- Reduce counterfeits

Compliance & Audit:
- SOX 404 audit trail
- GDPR data processing records
- Regulatory reporting
- Incident investigation

Dispute Resolution:
- Immutable evidence
- Cryptographic proof of sequence
- Non-repudiation
- Smart contract enforcement

Legal & Regulatory:
- Notarization (timestamp + hash)
- Smart contracts as legal agreements
- Autonomous enforcement
- Reduced litigation

Challenges:

Performance:
- Blockchain latency: 1-10 seconds/block
- YAWL needs: <1ms task latency
- Solution: Off-chain state channels

Scalability:
- Blockchain throughput: 100s tx/sec
- YAWL needs: 1000s tasks/sec
- Solution: Sharding or sidechain

Privacy:
- Blockchain transparency vs privacy
- GDPR "right to be forgotten"
- Solution: Zero-knowledge proofs

Cost:
- Gas fees per transaction
- Batch writing to reduce costs
- Proof-of-Stake (cheaper than PoW)

Timeline:
- Q4 2026: Research & prototype
- Q1 2027: MVP with Ethereum
- Q2 2027: Custom sidechain
- Q3 2027: Integration with YAWL
- Q4 2027: Production deployment
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
